README for JBrickBuilder 0.4.2 beta

News
- Building STEP support (experimental)

Bugfix
- weird/wrong part orientation when auto-align connections (FIXED)
- some functions not working with autoconnect off (FIXED)
- wrong part placement handling on repeat function disabled

Notes
- to run program you need Java runtime 6 or newer
- you need only the JAR
- runme.sh is an helper for Unix/Linux platform where JAR 
    is not considered "executable" (i.e. does not starts with a double click)

- version 0.1.0 connection database is incompatible: please update at first run.


Please read manual for installation and first run instructions.


